Then, their teachers would teach them one letter at a time and how to use strokes to connect the letters.&nbsp; Cursive handwriting is very efficient because it takes much less time than printing.&nbsp; For example, used bicycle or motorcycle helmets might have been involved in accidents that compromised the helmets&#39; structure or safety features.&nbsp; Another example is car seats and cribs for infants and children, which might have been damaged in some way unknown to you; because these products are essential to children&#39;s safety, it is better to purchase them new.&nbsp; Used car tires are also a bad idea for safety reasons; used tires might have worn treads that can lead to blowouts and other serious problems.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":1,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"showRuler":0,"showRFB":1},"leftText":"<p>Review your thesis statement and your writing web to plan the second body paragraph of your contest essay.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><img alt=\"The part of the writing web for your second body paragraph.
